definitions.definition: The rear body or compartment of some types of motor vehicle, especially one containing seats for passengers.
An old-style open passenger vehicle with a tonneau (rear compartment with seats).
examples: He has spent ten years lovingly restoring a rather luxurious tonneau with teak panelling and leather seats.
